********************************************************
| Use case                                                                            | Recommended Content-Type                                     |
| ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Sending **structured data** (text, numbers, lists, objects)                         | `application/json`                                           |
| Uploading **files** (images, videos, documents) — possibly *with extra form fields* | `multipart/form-data`                                        |
| Submitting **simple forms** (like HTML form POSTs)                                  | `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` or `multipart/form-data` |

✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅Sending request using fetch() API✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅
✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅Sending request using fetch() API✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅✅

const file = fileInputElement.files[0];
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append("file", file);
formData.append("title", "My Video");
formData.append("user_id", "101");
formData.append("description", "Beach trip vlog");

fetch(url, {
  method: "POST",
#----------Start: for json body--------
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer token_here",
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    pin: "1000",
  }),
#----------End: for json body--------
#----------Start: for FormData body--------
  headers: {
    "Authorization": "Bearer token_here",
  },
  body: formData,
#----------End: for FormData body--------
})
  .then((res) => res.json())
  .then((data) => {
    console.log("✅ Response:", data);
  })
  .catch((error) => {
    console.error("❌ Error:", error);
  });
